            "body": "@dyllandry Totally! Glad it helped. Also, FWIW, I was able to upgrade `eslint` to the latest version and get LSP diagnositics as expected by updating my LSP config to:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nrequire(\"mason-lspconfig\").setup({\r\n\tensure_installed = {\r\n-- ...\r\n\t\t\"eslint\",\r\n-- ...\r\n\t},\r\n})\r\n-- ... \r\nlspconfig.eslint.setup({\r\n\tcapabilities = capabilities,\r\n\tsettings = {\r\n\t\tworkingDirectories = { mode = \"auto\" },\r\n    experimental = {\r\n      useFlatConfig = false,\r\n    }\r\n\t},\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nMy guess is that this was silently failing when `eslint v4.9.0` was used, but after that, I started getting errors logged in neovim about the change from nested to flat configs, at which point I updated my config to the above ü§∑üèª ",
